<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@Vte{{}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}}} means to go somewhere, perform an action and return.
If necessary, the place where the remote action happens can be indicated by @HI{{de}}.
If the purpose is to go somewhere and move something, then @HI{{kara}} is used instead.

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{chotto tabakowo @KJ{{buy}}@EM{{tte @KJ{{come}}masu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I'm just popping out to buy some cigarettes.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{pedestal^place}}kara @KT{{koppu}}wo @KJ{{take}}@EM{{tte @KJ{{come}}masu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I'm going to fetch a glass from the kitchen.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@Vte{{}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}}} can indicate the beginning of a process when used with a verb
that indicates a process that takes some time to finish (e.g. @HI{{wakaru}}, @HI{{naru}}, @HI{{futoru}} etc.).

<table class="sentence" border=0>
